    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-05-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-05-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="77"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d77">
                <head>No. 790.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bragg</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-05-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 30, 1888</date>. (Received June
                        4.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 48.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to advise you that I have this
                    day transmitted copy of your views in the Cutting case, as set forth in your
                    dispatch No. 42, to Mr. Mariscal, and herewith inclose copy of my note
                    submitting the same.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwd. S. Bragg.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure in No. 48.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bragg</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Mariscal</persName>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-05-28">
                                <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 28, 1888</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to advise your excellency
                        that I am in receipt of a note of instruction from the Hon. T. F. Bayard,
                        Secretary of State, in reference to the Cutting contention, and, as I am
                        authorized by the terms of the instruction to do, I take great pleasure in
                        furnishing you a copy<note n="*" xml:id="d77fn1">For inclosure, see Doc. No.
                            785, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1189">p.
                            1189</ref>.</note>
                        <hi rend="italic">in extenso</hi>, that your excellency may be authentically
                        advised of the views of the Department of State of my Government in
                        reference to the pending contention.</p>
                    <p>I embrace this opportunity, etc.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwd. S. Bragg.</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
